  "text": "We report a comparison of outcomes of a series of 138 patients (207 knees) who underwent BSKA or ULKA at our institution. Patients undergoing ULKA would have the same risks and complications at their subsequent admission when they undergo a surgery for their contralateral knee, unlike BSKA patients [CITATION_1] .",
